The paper discusses the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques for forecasting spatial-temporal signals, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of dynamical systems theory, which suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) or systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of mutual information, which is a common measure in information theory and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of their proposed method with alternative feature selection methods, which suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
